SuGR Manual User


Welcome to SuGR (SAFIR02 Upload Gustave Roussy), the Shiny application that allows you to check, edit your files and submit them on Synapse.

1. Log in


To log in you have to enter your Synapse User Name and Password.



2. Upload your files


  • You can select multiple files at the same time.
  • If you don’t see your file, it means that the file you are trying to upload was not supported by SuGR. Please ensure that your file has either a .CEL/.CEL.bz2 or a .tsv extension. Otherwise, the warning below will show up.
  • On the side panel, you can see the list of files that will be uploaded on Synapse



a. CEL files


  • Click on “CEL” then “Browse”


Warning: Every time you will click on Browse, the previous list of files to upload will be deleted.



  • Select your file in the drop down menu




  • Once the files have been processed, click on “Upload ALL CEL on Synapse” to begin the transfer





b. NGS files


  • Click on “NGS” then “Browse”




Warning: Every time you will click on Browse, the previous list of files to upload will be deleted.


  • A discrepancy will be mark in red. You can edit the table by double clicking on the cell, select your correction in the drop down menu and type Enter after modification. You can also get some help by looking at the Sample Sheet Rules or the list of Gene Name files.





- Don’t forget to click on Save changes after editing.

Warning: Clicking again on the file in the drop down menu will erase your modifications.


  • The new version of your table can be download by clicking on “Download New Table”. The version of this table is the one edited by SuGR and yourself.



3. Warning color code


  • A green warning indicates that the file is correct and can be uploaded
  • An orange warning indicates that the file is incorrect but the problem has been corrected (ex: space found in file name) and the file orangecan be uploaded.
    Note that once the file has been rename, you can not click again on the drop down menu. You will have to upload it again
  • A red warning indicates that the file is incorrect and that a new version has to be edited and/or download.
  • Make sure that there are no red warnings before uploading on synapse.





4. Disconnecting


  • Click on “Close window” on the bottom right, to disconnect from Synapse and close the app. Note that all the temp files will be deleted as well.



5. Contact


If you need any help or requests, please contact Alicia TRAN DIEN (alicia.tran-dien@gustaveroussy.fr) from Gustave Roussy Bioinformatics plateform.
